R package meta (Schwarzer, 2007) provides the following statistical methods for meta-analysis.
1.	Fixed effect and random effects model:
o	Meta-analysis of continuous outcome data (metacont)
o	Meta-analysis of binary outcome data (metabin)
o	Meta-analysis of incidence rates (metainc)
o	Generic inverse variance meta-analysis (metagen)
o	Meta-analysis of single correlations (metacor)
o	Meta-analysis of single means (metamean)
o	Meta-analysis of single proportions (metaprop)
o	Meta-analysis of single incidence rates (metarate)
